    {
      "key": "610554ea-375a-4d85-9340-080410ea3f81",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Using the remaining items on your Project Planning Board and the feedback from your peers, continue to develop your Creative Coding Project. Each time you complete a goal, commit your code and move the tasks to the next column. There should only be one item in the “In Progress” column at a time, meaning that each item should be entirely completed before moving on to the next item.",
        "name": "Development",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "610554ea-375a-4d85-9340-080410ea3f81",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d64bc551-be07-45ce-87ac-cddd0430f237"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d5f43205-8967-4b72-be16-e54e2d2c82d6",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students prioritize the remaining tasks on their Project Planning Board based on feedback and self-assessment.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to work on the Creative Coding with the Console Project.",
        "progression_name": "Creative Coding with the Console Project",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Remind students to refer to their Project Planning Board to decide what tasks to work on during this time. You can also encourage students to request a code review from their peers as they work."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d5f43205-8967-4b72-be16-e54e2d2c82d6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d64bc551-be07-45ce-87ac-cddd0430f237"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "02b0a422-0577-4de2-ab89-58ff80f8b905",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "This is a good time to commit our code and save our new superclass and subclasses to the Backpack. Anytime we make changes to our programs, it is helpful to commit, or save, our work as a new version in case we need to revert to a previous version.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "02b0a422-0577-4de2-ab89-58ff80f8b905",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d64bc551-be07-45ce-87ac-cddd0430f237"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b427e52c-0bd3-4108-bb1d-72799f1208af",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Play the music clip to cue committing their code and saving their classes to the Backpack.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Using music to cue transitions helps create routines in the classroom. When students hear cues, they know it is time to transition to a specific activity. Emphasize to students what the music clip means, and be consistent with the use of the music clip to cue the activity.\n\nClick the blue play icon on the slide to play the music cue."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b427e52c-0bd3-4108-bb1d-72799f1208af",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d64bc551-be07-45ce-87ac-cddd0430f237"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5ae79900-3bb9-46c2-b730-19bad176f41d",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to respond to the End of Project Reflection prompt on the Creative Coding with the Console Project Planning Guide.",
        "name": "End of Project Reflection",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their thoughts and ideas with a neighbor."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5ae79900-3bb9-46c2-b730-19bad176f41d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "0f521947-046e-4465-b9c9-c1028d3bc9ea"
      }
    },
