    {
      "key": "c9fa7f37-ea9d-45ad-a861-efe64bdacb45",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete a short end-of-unit survey. Although their answers are anonymous, the aggregated data will be available to you once at least five students have completed the survey.",
        "name": "End of Unit Survey",
        "progression_name": "End of Unit Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c9fa7f37-ea9d-45ad-a861-efe64bdacb45",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4516301b-d4a7-4e90-bfee-8da95dcd41b9"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9072ca71-d16a-49ff-985f-186c278ffb9f",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Note**: The unit assessment project is adapted from the Unit 7 project in the Objects First version of the course. As such, there are criteria contained within the rubric that might not align with the current level of knowledge of students. You are encouraged to create a version of the rubric which you feel is fair for your students, given their trajectory within the CED-aligned version of the course.\n\nStudents work on the project throughout the unit to brainstorm, plan, and begin developing their program. Students then have three dedicated class periods to refine and complete their projects.\n\nIf there is not enough time for the three-day project, a one-day option achieves the targeted learning objectives and goals. If using this option, refer to the [**Creative Coding with The Theater Project 1-Day Lesson Plan**](https://studio.code.org/s/csa7-2023/lessons/14). While the one-day option covers the learning objectives and goals, it shortens planning and reflection time. Consider this tradeoff when deciding which version to use."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9072ca71-d16a-49ff-985f-186c278ffb9f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "b8f737e3-9423-4c2a-a9ef-f59e7e63b786"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a0b9bb1e-fc92-488e-8db7-5f9219b6bf36",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Before working towards your final benchmark, review the project requirements and rubric and evaluate your progress. Self-assessing your progress will help you identify which tasks to focus on during your project workdays.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Warm Up",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a0b9bb1e-fc92-488e-8db7-5f9219b6bf36",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "08aed1e6-8e3d-4bef-ad17-073b33d4d766",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students individually self-assess their project using the rubric on the last page of the Creative Coding with The Theater Project Planning Guide and review any remaining questions in the \"Need to Know\" column on page two.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What questions do you still have that need answering for this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share any questions they still have in their \"Need to Know\" column.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class.\n\nStudents may have questions that are unrelated or beyond the scope of the project. Encourage students to research these questions as extension activities. Focus this discussion on answering questions specific to the content covered in this unit and for the project."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "08aed1e6-8e3d-4bef-ad17-073b33d4d766",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0c15b720-19d5-4d04-b2a1-63ff3d10fc36",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students post tasks they want to complete for the third benchmark in the \"To Do\" column of their Project Planning Board."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0c15b720-19d5-4d04-b2a1-63ff3d10fc36",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b60e494c-bb85-430e-9bbe-6f448f5d2e3f",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Using the remaining items on your Project Planning Board and the feedback from your peers, continue to develop your Creative Coding Project. Each time you complete a goal, commit your code and move the tasks to the next column. There should only be one item in the “In Progress” column at a time, meaning that each item should be entirely completed before moving on to the next item.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Development",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b60e494c-bb85-430e-9bbe-6f448f5d2e3f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3e7bc227-66ea-4c8f-b94f-1634f17980cc",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students prioritize the remaining tasks on their Project Planning Board based on feedback and self-assessment.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to work on the Creative Coding with The Theater Project.",
        "progression_name": "Creative Coding with The Theater Project",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Remind students to refer to their Project Planning Board to decide what tasks to work on during this time. You can also encourage students to request a code review from their peers as they work."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3e7bc227-66ea-4c8f-b94f-1634f17980cc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "30f3e694-45cb-43f7-ace3-968b8682f619",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "One of the most important aspects of software engineering is an understanding of what it means for an item to be done. You may have considered an item to be done once you have finished writing it into your code. Others may consider it to be done after it has been thoroughly tested and reviewed for bugs. When working for a client, an item is considered to be done when requirements set by engineers and the client have been met.\n\nTo define what it means for an item to be done, software engineers write acceptance criteria for each item.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Acceptance Testing",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "30f3e694-45cb-43f7-ace3-968b8682f619",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ffc41abc-9721-442b-92eb-bc1132453f77",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***acceptance criteria*** and outline the steps for writing acceptance criteria in a scenario-based format.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Demonstrate an example of scenario-based acceptance criteria.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show the video – *Software Engineering: Acceptance Testing*.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Videos are used throughout the curriculum to spark discussions, supplement key concepts with additional explanations and examples, and expose students to the various roles and backgrounds of individuals in computer science.\n\nWhile interacting with the video, turn on closed captioning so students can also read along as they watch.\n\nTo encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FqIUpJg6MrgdtbFGLobSojOz0u1m5Jge1nMAjUqI5ZM/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ffc41abc-9721-442b-92eb-bc1132453f77",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d7a6433f-4468-4198-acc2-df23609ceaaa",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define ***acceptance testing***."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d7a6433f-4468-4198-acc2-df23609ceaaa",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8022210d-9191-47bd-9a79-8b3023344c79",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Now it’s your turn to write and test acceptance criteria for your user stories. Your reviewer should test your program and determine which of your user stories are complete and which ones still need work.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8022210d-9191-47bd-9a79-8b3023344c79",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0f84acc3-5521-426d-bc1b-a2d797b1ff5b",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to have students participate in the Code Review Call and Response."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0f84acc3-5521-426d-bc1b-a2d797b1ff5b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "356e4ff4-c623-4e72-8bcf-8dd28d3e1093",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to conduct a code review on their Creative Coding with The Theater Project. Have students write a code review request that includes acceptance criteria for their user stories. Afterward, students review their peer’s code and determine if the acceptance criteria are met.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Students may be at different points when it is time for the code review. Emphasize to students that their work does not need to be completed to get feedback. Remind students that the problem-solving and development process is iterative and that receiving feedback from peers while they are working can help give them additional insights, perspectives, and guidance."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "356e4ff4-c623-4e72-8bcf-8dd28d3e1093",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5a6d3759-0a6c-4288-be09-cd989ab14ac4",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students update their Project Planning Board with any tasks they completed, changed, or added.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "You can review the Project Planning Board as an optional completion assessment."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5a6d3759-0a6c-4288-be09-cd989ab14ac4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "d12b9c4e-eb62-481d-b42d-5f788ed468e7"
      }
    },
