        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Students may be at different points when it is time for the code review. Emphasize to students that their work does not need to be completed to get feedback. Remind students that the problem-solving and development process is iterative and that receiving feedback from peers while they are working can help give them additional insights, perspectives, and guidance."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9c451c13-d79b-4387-b305-0e49f7090929",
        "lesson_activity.key": "fbc6dfe4-e6c0-48f9-9126-ce505465cc59"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8b66768f-8e13-445b-917a-d3bddd7c9aa3",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students update their Project Planning Board with any tasks they completed, changed, or added.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "You can review the Project Planning Board as an optional completion assessment."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8b66768f-8e13-445b-917a-d3bddd7c9aa3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "fbc6dfe4-e6c0-48f9-9126-ce505465cc59"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c1498294-f79c-49b6-9ec4-42970605b0d4",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We are almost done with our project! You should be proud of what you have accomplished in this unit and this project.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Warm Up",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c1498294-f79c-49b6-9ec4-42970605b0d4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1270720e-3c59-4cd0-87e7-0ed8993220ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c4f9a81e-6c41-488b-8ec1-8af90bb63704",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What are you most proud of about your project so far?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share what they are proud of about their project."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c4f9a81e-6c41-488b-8ec1-8af90bb63704",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1270720e-3c59-4cd0-87e7-0ed8993220ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6e7b53b7-3ada-4164-a976-f5bb1fce17c1",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "It's time to put the finishing touches on our projects!\n\nUsing the remaining items on your Project Planning Board and the feedback from your peers, continue to develop your Creative Coding Project. Each time you complete a goal, commit your code and move the tasks to the next column. There should only be one item in the “In Progress” column at a time, meaning that each item should be entirely completed before moving on to the next item.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Development",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6e7b53b7-3ada-4164-a976-f5bb1fce17c1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1270720e-3c59-4cd0-87e7-0ed8993220ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c6b005e0-91a2-4741-adf9-f2fd29cc5825",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to finish and submit their Creative Coding with The Theater Project.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Remind students that they may not complete every item on their Project Planning Board or Project Backlog, and that is okay! Software engineers have to make decisions all the time about which features are most important. The purpose of creating Project Planning Boards and Project Backlogs is to focus on completing the most important items first."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c6b005e0-91a2-4741-adf9-f2fd29cc5825",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1270720e-3c59-4cd0-87e7-0ed8993220ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "dc9a8ddb-b9b3-4679-876a-7d1f8e3d09cc",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Congratulations! You have completed your creative coding project for this unit. Let's show off our work through a Gallery Walk so you can share your work with your classmates.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Peer Presentations",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "dc9a8ddb-b9b3-4679-876a-7d1f8e3d09cc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1270720e-3c59-4cd0-87e7-0ed8993220ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e49c045b-1488-4d98-80e8-5ad50e38a0a5",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student several sticky notes.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students participate in a Gallery Walk to view each other's programs and leave sticky notes noting what they like about the program."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e49c045b-1488-4d98-80e8-5ad50e38a0a5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1270720e-3c59-4cd0-87e7-0ed8993220ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "00c7eadb-d124-4dd1-997f-e2e766f0e2e9",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to respond to the End of Project Reflection prompt on the Creative Coding with The Theater Project Planning Guide.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Wrap Up",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their thoughts and ideas with a neighbor.\n\nGather the Project Planning Boards to reuse in the next unit."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "00c7eadb-d124-4dd1-997f-e2e766f0e2e9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1270720e-3c59-4cd0-87e7-0ed8993220ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fc41f330-0024-4acf-9ce7-883900d14c9b",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students complete a short end-of-unit survey. Although their answers are anonymous, the aggregated data will be available to you once at least five students have completed the survey.",
        "name": "End of Unit Survey",
        "progression_name": "End of Unit Survey",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "We also have a teacher end-of-unit survey to learn more about how the unit went for you and your students. While students take their survey, please complete [**this end of unit survey for teachers**](https://studio.code.org/form/teacher_end_of_unit_survey?survey_data%5Bunit_number%5D=7) as well. Your feedback is valued and appreciated!"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fc41f330-0024-4acf-9ce7-883900d14c9b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1270720e-3c59-4cd0-87e7-0ed8993220ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d4897732-222b-463f-902a-2d4b44f137a5",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d4897732-222b-463f-902a-2d4b44f137a5",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1270720e-3c59-4cd0-87e7-0ed8993220ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fa46243b-438b-4ec8-ae81-4f79344dbaf3",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Creative Coding with The Theater Project Planning Guide:** Use the rubric in the Creative Coding with The Theater Project Planning Guide to assess the projects.",
        "name": "Assessment: Grading the Project"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fa46243b-438b-4ec8-ae81-4f79344dbaf3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1270720e-3c59-4cd0-87e7-0ed8993220ac"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "25b263d4-37a8-492c-9291-635e29aa8488",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Note**: The unit assessment project is adapted from the Unit 7 project in the Objects First version of the course. As such, there are criteria contained within the rubric that might not align with the current level of knowledge of students. You are encouraged to create a version of the rubric which you feel is fair for your students, given their trajectory within the CED-aligned version of the course."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "25b263d4-37a8-492c-9291-635e29aa8488",
        "lesson_activity.key": "8222d358-cfcd-46c6-9e4d-222ee6045c6c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1cfe517f-cffc-48f5-8d81-0db1063da74a",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Before working towards your final benchmark, review the project requirements and rubric and evaluate your progress. Self-assessing your progress will help you identify which tasks to focus on during your project workdays.",
        "name": "Project Self-Assessment",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1cfe517f-cffc-48f5-8d81-0db1063da74a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "06dd29ff-18bd-4563-989d-f9ab134d387d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "94ad8287-ad8f-4953-9a3a-d3d9f07bba34",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students individually self-assess their project using the rubric on the last page of the Creative Coding with The Theater Project Planning Guide and review any remaining questions in the \"Need to Know\" column on page two.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What questions do you still have that need answering for this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share any questions they still have in their \"Need to Know\" column.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class.\n\nStudents may have questions that are unrelated or beyond the scope of the project. Encourage students to research these questions as extension activities. Focus this discussion on answering questions specific to the content covered in this unit and for the project."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "94ad8287-ad8f-4953-9a3a-d3d9f07bba34",
        "lesson_activity.key": "06dd29ff-18bd-4563-989d-f9ab134d387d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "cde0de90-2b0b-47c9-b6f8-a9f36579dc95",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students post tasks they want to complete for the third benchmark in the \"To Do\" column of their Project Planning Board."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "cde0de90-2b0b-47c9-b6f8-a9f36579dc95",
        "lesson_activity.key": "06dd29ff-18bd-4563-989d-f9ab134d387d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7f78b71c-022b-456f-b92f-c4542956616e",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Using the remaining items on your Project Planning Board and the feedback from your peers, continue to develop your Creative Coding Project. Each time you complete a goal, commit your code and move the tasks to the next column. There should only be one item in the “In Progress” column at a time, meaning that each item should be entirely completed before moving on to the next item.",
        "name": "Development",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7f78b71c-022b-456f-b92f-c4542956616e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e2a688bb-1dd5-48fe-824e-bb47c8a193be"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c09ce4a2-7cde-4ef7-839b-9f6d160481a7",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students prioritize the remaining tasks on their Project Planning Board based on feedback and self-assessment.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to work on the Creative Coding with The Theater Project.",
        "progression_name": "Creative Coding with The Theater Project",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Remind students to refer to their Project Planning Board to decide what tasks to work on during this time. You can also encourage students to request a code review from their peers as they work."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c09ce4a2-7cde-4ef7-839b-9f6d160481a7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e2a688bb-1dd5-48fe-824e-bb47c8a193be"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6bae0408-bc16-4512-a89d-de84eb07a787",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "This is a good time to commit our code and save our new superclass and subclasses to the Backpack. Anytime we make changes to our programs, it is helpful to commit, or save, our work as a new version in case we need to revert to a previous version.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6bae0408-bc16-4512-a89d-de84eb07a787",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e2a688bb-1dd5-48fe-824e-bb47c8a193be"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5289bec4-5f6e-409e-a394-b2d3d722c67d",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Play the music clip to cue committing their code and saving their classes to the Backpack.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Using music to cue transitions helps create routines in the classroom. When students hear cues, they know it is time to transition to a specific activity. Emphasize to students what the music clip means, and be consistent with the use of the music clip to cue the activity.\n\nClick the blue play icon on the slide to play the music cue."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5289bec4-5f6e-409e-a394-b2d3d722c67d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e2a688bb-1dd5-48fe-824e-bb47c8a193be"
      }
    },
    {
